title.narrative: Output 1.2: Health and nutrition service delivery points in targeted districts have the capacity to deliver quality MNCH, HIV and nutrition services for all children and promote healthy behaviors.

description.narrative: A total of 67,638 children under 5 (35,171 M, 32,467 F) and 287,218 care givers, internal displaced persons, and host communities reached with integrated Health, Nutrition, HIV, ECD and WASH services. There is now increased access to MNCH, HIV and nutrition services followed by investing about 1.5 million USD on systems strengthening including capacity building, supply chain integration, creation of systems such as continuous epidemiological platform and support to district implementation plans. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/12/2019
